replies.body:
Just a heads-up for people saying that Trump won the majority of the votes, Hillary Clinton won 47.6% (59,092,337 ) of the national votes, whilst Donald Trump won 47.5% (58,967,470) as of the end of the vote counting.

The reason why Trump won is because of the First Past The Post system, which the American democratic system takes to a ridiculous degree. Trump won because the states he won were worth more points, not because he had more votes.
